extends base.jade
-load staticfiles
| {% load pipeline %}

block head
  link(rel='stylesheet', href='{% static "stylesheets/materials.css" %}')

block body
  div#skrollr-body
    section#materials-slide
      div.bcg
        div.hsContainer
          div.hsContent 
            div.header
              h5 <a href="/">⟵ Back to MakeMIT site</a>
            h1 Materials & Tools
            p 
              | See the list below for what we're providing you to hack with. 
              | We suggest all hackers bring a laptop. Other than that, leave 
              | it up to us! If you'd like to see something not on the list below, 
              | fill out the form linked below,
              | or put it in your registration form. We might be able to provide it, 
              | otherwise you're free to bring something off-the-shelf as long as it 
              | is pre-approved. Please note that any other materials will be confiscated 
              | at registration.
            div.ui.stackable.one.column.grid
              div.row
                div.center.aligned.center.floated.column
                  a(href="http://goo.gl/forms/eHCBps6KRE")
                    div#register.ui.button Materials Suggestion Form

            div.ui.divider

            div.header
              h2 Featured Materials
            div.ui.stackable.divided.two.column.grid.segment
              div.equal.height.row
                div.column
                  div.ui.divided.items
                    
                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="http://www.sdtimes.com/images/0310.sdt-kinoma-create.png")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="http://kinoma.com/create/about/") Kinoma Create
                        div.meta Kinoma
                        div.description
                          | Kinoma Create is the JavaScript-powered Internet of Things construction kit. Kinoma Create's 
                          | mission is to power the next wave of connected device prototyping. It's a pro-developer 
                          | experience that integrates hardware, software, and tools conceived expressly to be powerful, 
                          | approachable, and fast.

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="http://ecx.images-amazon.com/images/I/41Eh4W7cuiL._SX342_.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="http://www.8020.net/T-Slot-1.asp") 25mm Aluminum Extrusions
                        div.meta 80/20
                        div.description
                          | This adjustable, modular framing material, assembled with simple 
                          | hand tools, is a perfect solution for custom machine frames, guarding, 
                          | enclosures, displays, workstations, prototyping, and beyond.
                    
                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/wordpressprod/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/front-view.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="https://www.thalmic.com/en/myo/") Myo Armband
                        div.meta Thalmic Labs
                        div.description
                          | Myo motion control and gesture control armband bracelet uses arm muscle activity and 
                          | EMG signals to control digital devices over Bluetooth 4.0 Low Energy.

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="http://www.raspberrypi.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Pi2ModB1GB_-comp.jpeg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="http://www.raspberrypi.org/products/raspberry-pi-2-model-b/") Raspberry Pi 2
                        div.meta Raspberry Pi
                        div.description
                          | The Raspberry Pi 2 Model B is the second generation Raspberry Pi, with a 900MHz quad-core 
                          | ARM Cortex-A7 CPU (for ~6x performance), 1GB LPDDR2 SDRAM (for 2x memory), and complete 
                          | compatibility with Raspberry Pi 1

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="http://www.atmel.com/Images/ATmega328P_Xplained_Angle_th.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="http://www.atmel.com/tools/mega168-xmini.aspx") Xplained Mini
                        div.meta Atmel
                        div.description
                          | The Atmel ATmega328P Xplained Mini evalutation kit is a hardware platform for evaluating the 
                          | Atmel ATmega328P microcontroller. The evaluation kit comes with a fully integrated debugger 
                          | that provides seamless integration with Atmel Studio 6.2 or later. The kit provides access 
                          | to the features of the ATmega328P enabling easy integration of the device in a custom design.

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="http://makerbot-blog.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/White_HERO_Rep.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="http://store.makerbot.com/") 3D Printers
                        div.meta MakerBot 
                        div.description
                          | The easiest and most versatile way to get from 3D model to 3D print

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="http://mdm.boschwebservices.com/files/Dremel%20F0133000PA,%203000%20(EN,%20ES)%20r24615v15.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="http://www.dremel.com/en-us/Tools/Pages/ToolDetail.aspx?pid=3000") Dremel 3000
                        div.meta Dremel 
                        div.description
                          | The Dremel 3000 is the result of upgrading Dremel's most popular rotary 
                          | tool using user-requested features to improve the tool’s design and ergonomics.  
                          | The ability to use all existing Dremel rotary tool accessories and most attachments 
                          | let the 3000 complete a wide range of applications including cutting, grinding, sanding,
                          | carving and polishing a variety of materials.

                div.column
                  div.ui.divided.items

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="https://cdn.sparkfun.com//assets/parts/1/0/1/3/9/13097-06.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="https://www.sparkfun.com/products/13097") Edison Arduino Dev Kit
                        div.meta Intel
                        div.description
                          | The Intel® Edison is an ultra small computing platform that will change
                          | the way you look at embedded electronics. Powered by 
                          | the Intel® Atom™ SoC dual-core CPU and including an integrated WiFi, 
                          | Bluetooth LE, and a 70-pin connector to attach a veritable slew of 
                          | shield-like “Blocks” which can be stacked on top of each other. It’s no 
                          | wonder how this little guy is lowering the barrier of entry on the world of electronics!
                    
                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="https://dbvc4uanumi2d.cloudfront.net/cdn/4.3.11/wp-content/themes/oculus/img/order/dk2-product.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="https://www.oculus.com/dk2/") DK2
                        div.meta Oculus
                        div.description
                          | The Oculus Rift Development Kit 2 (DK2) is a development kit meant for developers 
                          | that want to create virtual reality content for the upcoming consumer version of the Oculus Rift.

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="http://dri1.img.digitalrivercontent.net/Storefront/Company/msintl/images/English/en-INTL-Kinect-for-Windows-Commercial-74Z-00001/en-INTL-L-Kinect-for-Windows-Commercial-74Z-00001-mnco.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/kinectforwindows/meetkinect/default.aspx") Kinect V2
                        div.meta Microsoft 
                        div.description
                          | A set of technologies that enable humans to interact naturally with computers, 
                          | the Kinect for Windows v2 sensor and free software development kit (SDK) 2.0 
                          | provide developers with the foundation needed to create and deploy interactive 
                          | applications that respond to peoples’ natural movements, gestures, and voice commands.

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="https://www.fabtolab.com/image/cache/data/Boards/Tessel/tessel-top-900x700.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="https://tessel.io/") Tessel
                        div.meta Technical Machine 
                        div.description
                          | Tessel is a microcontroller that runs JavaScript. 
                          | It's Node-compatible and ships with Wifi built in. 
                          | Use it to easily make physical devices that connect to the web.

                    

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="http://www.stratasys.com/~/media/en/3D%20Printers/Idea%20Series/uPrint%20SE/uprint_se_3d_printer.ashx")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="http://www.stratasys.com/3d-printers/idea-series/uprint-se") Stratasys UPrint
                        div.meta Stratasys 
                        div.description
                          | The uPrint SE offers larger ABSplus models and offers networking for easy sharing. 
                          | It’s a perfect solution for small teams who know 3D modeling is the key to effective prototyping and communication.

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="https://markforged.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/MF2014_HomeHero_R1_MK1.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="https://markforged.com/mark-one/") Mark One
                        div.meta MarkForged
                        div.description
                          | Along with the printer's novel material capabilities, the Mark One's revolutionary print 
                          | bed clicks into place with 10 micron accuracy – allowing you to pause a print, remove the 
                          | bed, add components, click the bed back in and then continue the print in the exact same 
                          | position to easily embed electronics, sensors, ball bearings, hard mounting point and more into your parts.

                    div.item
                      div.row
                        div.ui.image
                          img(src="http://mdm.boschwebservices.com/files/8050_hero-lg%20r118733v15.jpg")
                      div.content
                        h3.ui.header 
                          a(href="http://www.dremel.com/en-us/Tools/Pages/ToolDetail.aspx?pid=8050#.VOi8V1PF9Eg") Dremel Micro
                        div.meta Dremel 
                        div.description
                          | Brilliantly powerful, the Dremel Micro is the perfect combination of size, ergonomics 
                          | and power that make it the ultimate tool for both precise and light duty DIY tasks. 
                          | Designed to be held between the thumb and forefinger like a pencil, the Dremel Micro 
                          | allows a grip that is close to the work-piece for superior maneuverability and control. 
                          | To illuminate projects, the Dremel Micro has LED lights built uniquely into the nose cap 
                          | to aid in vision and accuracy.

